BOLA BAMIGBOLA Seven people on Saturday lost their lives in a fatal road crash that occurred along Osogbo-Ikirun Road in Osun State. The accident involved a truck with the number plate, FST 597 XY and a commercial space wagon with the number plate JJJ 59 CJ. All passengers, except one, on board died on the spot. Sources near the scene of the accident said it occurred around 7.30am. Giving details of the crash, the Osun Sector Commander, Federal Road Safety Corps, Peter Oke, gave the name of the driver of the commercial bus as Sheriff Azeez. He said five males and two females lost their lives in the crash, adding that the only survivor in the accident had been taken to the Ladoke Akintola University of Technology Teaching Hospital, Osogbo. He said, “The deceased have been taken to the morgue of the teaching hospital. The crash might have been caused by lack of concentration by the drivers. We urge drivers to ensure strict adherence to safety measures while driving.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com  